# beagle — environment variables
#
# Copy to `.env` for local overrides. On Vercel, set these in Project → Settings →
# Environment Variables (never commit secrets). Vars without the VITE_ prefix are
# server-side only and are never shipped to the browser (Section 6).

# Public site URL for Open Graph / Twitter link previews (no trailing slash).
# Example: https://beagle-demo.vercel.app
VITE_SITE_URL=

# --- Claude hero-variant proposals (FR-C1/FR-C2 — server-side only) ---------
# The Anthropic API key lives ONLY server-side (api/propose-challenger.js). With
# no key set, the AI toggle returns 501 and the client falls back to the local
# simulated stub — the optimisation loop never breaks. Under `npm run dev` the
# Vite dev middleware loads this file so a local key is picked up automatically.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# Optional model override; defaults to claude-opus-4-8.
ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8
#
# The PowerPoint report route (api/generate-report.js, FR-G3) REUSES the same
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (and ANTHROPIC_MODEL) — no separate key. With no key set it
# renders a deterministic .pptx from the run summary, clearly labelled
# "generated without Claude" (Section 6 graceful fallback).

# --- Supabase persistence (FR-D2/D3, FR-B, FR-E1, FR-F — server-side only) ---
# When these are set, api/ routes persist experiments, cookie assignments,
# results, token spend and guardrails to Postgres. When UNSET, Beagle falls back
# to the in-memory stores (no behaviour change). See supabase/migrations/0001_init.sql.
#
# Project URL (e.g. https://abcd1234.supabase.co). Used by BOTH server + client clients.
SUPABASE_URL=
# Anon (public) key — RLS-gated, safe to ship to the browser. Client-direct reads only.
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# Service-role key — BYPASSES RLS. SERVER-SIDE ONLY (api/ routes). NEVER ship to the
# browser and never prefix with VITE_. This is the key api/ writes use.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
# Supabase access token for the Management API / CLI migrations (`supabase db push`).
# Can double as SUPABASE_MCP_TOKEN. Local tooling only; never shipped.
SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# --- Legacy / unused by this route ------------------------------------------
# The challenger proxy now calls Claude via the Anthropic SDK. The old
# OpenAI-compatible LLM_* vars are no longer read by api/propose-challenger.js
# and can be left unset. (Kept here only to document the migration.)
# LLM_API_KEY=
# LLM_API_BASE=
# LLM_MODEL=
